text: Molino is an unincorporated community in Audrain County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called Molino was established in 1882, and remained in operation until 1957. The community's name commemorates the Battle of Molino del Rey. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Audrain County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Molino, Missouri
